Key Match Events: Evan Mobley finished with 25 points, eight rebounds, and three blocks, the most impactful player on the floor.
Scottie Barnes ended up with 9 points, six rebounds, and five assists.
Immanuel Quickley was lost to a right pelvic contusion after a rough fall in the second quarter.
Chris Boucher led the Raptors with 18 points off the bench.
Pre-Game Insights: Raptors coach Darko Rajaković emphasized Scottie Barnes' improvement and development, stating it will be a great year for him to learn what it takes to be a franchise player.
Cleveland's new head coach Kenny Atkinson discussed pushing Evan Mobley in new directions and emphasized the importance of Mobley's defense.
Post-Match Reflections: Scottie Barnes acknowledged the need to be more aggressive on the ball when playing in the zone.
Chris Boucher reflected on the game, stating it was probably good for the young team to get slapped in the face.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Raptors wore purple and black uniforms from the Vince Carter era.
Gradey Dick continues to attack closeouts aggressively and had a pump fake/relocate combo.
Jamal Shead had a nifty floater for his first NBA bucket and some nice moments as a defender and playmaker.
Jonathan Mogbo hit his first NBA three-pointer.
Others: Raptors coach Darko Rajaković called a timeout to challenge a play, but no foul was called, so there was nothing to challenge.
